subtests.name: WebGL test #0: Unable to fetch WebGL rendering context for Canvas
WebGL test #1: gl = getWebGL(1, 1, null, [ 0, 0, 0, 0 ], 1, 0) should be non-null. Was null
WebGL test #2: gl.getContextAttributes().stencil should be false. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #3: gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_BITS) == 0 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #4: Unable to fetch WebGL rendering context for Canvas
WebGL test #5: gl = getWebGL(1, 1, { alpha: true, depth: false, stencil: false, antialias: false }, [ 0, 0, 0, 0 ], 1, 0) should be non-null. Was null
WebGL test #6: gl.getParameter(gl.ALPHA_BITS) >= 8 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #7: gl.getParameter(gl.RED_BITS) >= 8 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #8: gl.getParameter(gl.GREEN_BITS) >= 8 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #9: gl.getParameter(gl.BLUE_BITS) >= 8 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #10: gl.getParameter(gl.DEPTH_BITS) == 0 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #11: gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_BITS) == 0 should be true. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #12: contextAttribs = gl.getContextAttributes() should be non-null. Threw exception TypeError: gl is null
WebGL test #13: contextAttribs.alpha == true should be true. Threw exception TypeError: contextAttribs is null
